In Antwarp Pbuno Aprill 1681
th
S in answer to yd of 18: pass, as soone I shall have yd advise concerning goods
from the north, shall send you may orders to provide a parcell, for towards the
latter end of this month is our uswall time to demand goods from theme
& seeng the hambourgh shipping then over, so supose wee shall finde goods
to content I am sorry, that yd clothier doth not stand to his promise indeed
yd writing of haueing 20 p. did in corridg mee to desire tthem, for wanted
an assortment &did still which is no small disapointement to mee
for I love to have my whare housed assorted off ull, lo in case non yett
send forward pray dispatch some thought itt should be butt 5 peeces
as best you can gett them & leave he rest there for our grecctest demand
for them will be att a stand in a short while nothwithstanding wee
have occasions for them all the yeare long, so a pemy wil may be
accepted off. I observe what you say as to yd kersyes to barter against
tjkes Ill make a tryall butt pray lett mee know the neare
price they cost, witth djing ball aboard & so rest on
London Will Scuwen
Ah In Antwarp Bns Aprill 81
aS. my last to you was on the 25 past sence recd yd of 18 ditto I take
notice what you say concerning the sending ferward of our callicois
if my instruction be observed 6 bales off cottons will bring them all
over, & I supose there are many bj landars now in loading, so that they
might be shipped all att a time & in case you iudge oele bale to little
in one bottom, ship 2 bales in each vessel butt make nt so that the
brouwed modecolleurs be first dispatched & when these all schipped
you will loose no knighs mony for I had butt yeasterday aletter from
mr. Coats, by which he did advise mee not to venter as yett till suither
order & that the bale seased be cleared, where fore I am not a little shy &
should dare not genter so, as wee die the last parcell tis the fault of p
of Brussels, that, that plott is discovered, whoever itt could have happined
to us where fore tis goods oprovided for the worst so then do as you
ind gebest p for I ruther pay custome then loose all as, you say I hope
the packett of lace is with you bij this time & thought I have no time
now, to send such an acett as you desire never the less you wll
make shilst up on my invoycer to dispose of them to content
whoever itt will follos pr next so remaine
